quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  61,1,"Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is on the earth glorifies Allah. And He is the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  61,2,O you who believe! Why do you say that which you do not do
  61,3,Most hateful it is with Allah that you say that which you do not do
  61,4,"Verily, Allah loves those who fight in His cause in rows as if they were a solid structure"
  61,5,"And when Musa said to his people: \"O my people! Why do you annoy me while you know certainly that I am the Messenger of Allah to you So, when they turned away (from the path of Allah), Allah turned their hearts away (from the right path). And Allah guides not the people who are rebellious"
  61,6,"And (remember) when `Isa, son of Maryam, said: \"O Children of Israel! I am the Messenger of Allah unto you, confirming the Tawrah [which came] before me, and giving glad tidings of a Messenger to come after me, whose name shall be Ahmad. \"But when he came to them with clear proofs, they said: \"This is plain magic"
  61,7,"And who does more wrong than the one who invents a lie against Allah, while he is being invited to Islam And Allah guides not the people who are wrongdoers"
  61,8,They intend to put out the Light of Allah with their mouths. But Allah will bring His Light to perfection even though the disbelievers hate (it)
  61,9,He it is Who has sent His Messenger with guidance and the religion of truth to make it victorious over all religions even though idolators hate (it)